If we only had to display the ID, that was super simple.

4
00:00:10,020 --> 00:00:12,360
If I go to controller here.

5
00:00:12,360 --> 00:00:15,810
And let me add a debugging point on the product controller.

6
00:00:15,810 --> 00:00:17,490
Index action.

7
00:00:17,490 --> 00:00:19,110
Refresh that.

8
00:00:19,110 --> 00:00:23,190
If I examine the obj product list, you will notice

9
00:00:23,190 --> 00:00:28,020
we have category ID that is populated for our products.

10
00:00:28,020 --> 00:00:31,440
But we need to populate this category navigation

11
00:00:31,440 --> 00:00:33,990
property because inside there we have

12
00:00:33,990 --> 00:00:37,530
category name that we can access.

13
00:00:37,530 --> 00:00:40,560
So basically based on the foreign key relation

14
00:00:40,560 --> 00:00:43,533
we need this category to be populated.

15
00:00:44,430 --> 00:00:48,393
How can we do that smartly using EF core?

16
00:00:49,500 --> 00:00:52,290
Or that we have something called as include

17
00:00:52,290 --> 00:00:56,160
that will automatically include the navigation properties

18
00:00:56,160 --> 00:00:58,470
based on the foreign key relation

19
00:00:58,470 --> 00:01:01,443
and it is provided by the EFO team.

20
00:01:02,670 --> 00:01:05,459
So how can we use that?

21
00:01:05,459 --> 00:01:09,060
We will have to add that to our core repository

22
00:01:09,060 --> 00:01:11,670
because that is the method that we are using

23
00:01:11,670 --> 00:01:14,970
in the controller to get all the product.

24
00:01:14,970 --> 00:01:15,990
That is...

25
00:01:15,990 --> 00:01:17,370
Where is that?

26
00:01:17,370 --> 00:01:18,453
Right here.

27
00:01:19,290 --> 00:01:22,290
Now before I add that in the get all logic,

28
00:01:22,290 --> 00:01:24,060
let me show you how that will work

29
00:01:24,060 --> 00:01:26,610
with directly application DB context.

30
00:01:26,610 --> 00:01:31,290
Right here we have underscore db.products.

31
00:01:31,290 --> 00:01:34,170
On there we have something called as include.

32
00:01:34,170 --> 00:01:37,500
And you can see right here it says specifies

33
00:01:37,500 --> 00:01:41,013
related entities to include in the query string.

34
00:01:41,970 --> 00:01:43,620
So let me add that.

35
00:01:43,620 --> 00:01:47,100
And what we want to include, we can write that

36
00:01:47,100 --> 00:01:50,760
by saying U goes to U dot.

37
00:01:50,760 --> 00:01:53,640
And we want to include category.

38
00:01:53,640 --> 00:01:56,490
That is how what will happen is that category

39
00:01:56,490 --> 00:02:00,450
will automatically be populated when it retrieves

40
00:02:00,450 --> 00:02:04,053
all the product based on the foreign key relation.

41
00:02:05,100 --> 00:02:09,240
So this is great, but how can we add this same logic

42
00:02:09,240 --> 00:02:12,243
inside the get all that we have right here?

43
00:02:13,200 --> 00:02:15,930
For that we will have to add a logic.

44
00:02:15,930 --> 00:02:18,420
But I want to show you one more thing.

45
00:02:18,420 --> 00:02:22,110
Right now we only have category that we want to include.

46
00:02:22,110 --> 00:02:24,990
But if you had to include more properties,

47
00:02:24,990 --> 00:02:28,050
you can add multiple include statements.

48
00:02:28,050 --> 00:02:31,530
And rather than category, if this was something else,

49
00:02:31,530 --> 00:02:33,603
you can include that as well.

50
00:02:34,530 --> 00:02:38,490
So include can have multiple variables like category,

51
00:02:38,490 --> 00:02:41,790
category ID, maybe you have cover type

52
00:02:41,790 --> 00:02:45,033
or something else that could also be included.

53
00:02:46,020 --> 00:02:48,210
We want to make sure that our repository

54
00:02:48,210 --> 00:02:50,043
can handle that scenario.

55
00:02:50,940 --> 00:02:54,630
For that what I will do is we can have a nullable.

56
00:02:54,630 --> 00:02:56,640
Include properties.

57
00:02:56,640 --> 00:02:58,233
And that will be string.

58
00:02:59,070 --> 00:03:01,590
Now right here it is a link operator.

59
00:03:01,590 --> 00:03:05,760
When we are saying it will be a string, what do we expect?

60
00:03:05,760 --> 00:03:08,340
Basically we are saying that if someone gives us

61
00:03:08,340 --> 00:03:11,760
category or category ID, based on that

62
00:03:11,760 --> 00:03:14,340
we can build to include properties.

63
00:03:14,340 --> 00:03:18,330
Now category ID is just an ID, so things will not work.

64
00:03:18,330 --> 00:03:20,520
So for an example I am saying

65
00:03:20,520 --> 00:03:22,230
let's say there are two things,

66
00:03:22,230 --> 00:03:26,343
category and cover type, that a user has to include.

67
00:03:27,180 --> 00:03:29,910
So if in include properties they provide that

68
00:03:29,910 --> 00:03:32,100
with a comma separated string,

69
00:03:32,100 --> 00:03:35,340
then we can add that in the include statement

70
00:03:35,340 --> 00:03:38,220
when we are building the query here.

71
00:03:38,220 --> 00:03:41,640
One thing that is very very important here

72
00:03:41,640 --> 00:03:46,640
is this category must match exactly that you see right here.

73
00:03:47,040 --> 00:03:51,120
If you use a lowercase C here, things will not work

74
00:03:51,120 --> 00:03:53,460
because let's say if you try a lowercase

75
00:03:53,460 --> 00:03:56,940
category you can see it is not working.

76
00:03:56,940 --> 00:03:58,890
So it must match what you see

77
00:03:58,890 --> 00:04:01,950
in the include statement that is working here.

78
00:04:01,950 --> 00:04:04,710
And that is exactly what you should pass

79
00:04:04,710 --> 00:04:07,833
in the string parameter right here.

80
00:04:08,670 --> 00:04:12,450
Let me add this inside the interface as well.

81
00:04:12,450 --> 00:04:16,320
We have the interface repository interface.

82
00:04:16,320 --> 00:04:17,370
Get all.

83
00:04:17,370 --> 00:04:19,440
And when we are getting something,

84
00:04:19,440 --> 00:04:22,860
at that point also we want to include properties.

85
00:04:22,860 --> 00:04:26,103
So we will add that logic, input the places.

86
00:04:27,390 --> 00:04:30,900
Then we need the actual logic of adding that.

87
00:04:30,900 --> 00:04:33,150
Basically we will first check here

88
00:04:33,150 --> 00:04:36,093
if include properties is not null.

89
00:04:38,010 --> 00:04:40,770
In that case, well rather than not here

90
00:04:40,770 --> 00:04:44,523
I will rather check string is null or empty.

91
00:04:48,150 --> 00:04:52,350
So if it is not null and empty, we will add a not sign.

92
00:04:52,350 --> 00:04:55,230
Then we want to include properties.

93
00:04:55,230 --> 00:04:57,993
Like what we see on the top right here.

94
00:04:59,190 --> 00:05:03,120
But we will be receiving them as comma separated values.

95
00:05:03,120 --> 00:05:05,400
So we will have to split them.

96
00:05:05,400 --> 00:05:09,123
We will have a for each and I will say include.

97
00:05:10,050 --> 00:05:14,550
Prop in, include properties.split.

98
00:05:14,550 --> 00:05:18,030
And we will split them by a new character.

99
00:05:18,030 --> 00:05:19,743
Which will be comma.

100
00:05:20,820 --> 00:05:24,750
And here I will say string, split options.

101
00:05:24,750 --> 00:05:27,540
Dot remove empty entries.

102
00:05:27,540 --> 00:05:32,070
So if any entry is empty it will remove those.

103
00:05:32,070 --> 00:05:35,820
And let me split this in a separate line.

104
00:05:35,820 --> 00:05:38,673
So it is easier to read and understand.

105
00:05:40,140 --> 00:05:43,710
Then where we have the query we will say query is equal

106
00:05:43,710 --> 00:05:47,336
to query.include, and we want to include

107
00:05:47,336 --> 00:05:51,420
the include prop that we are splitting.

108
00:05:51,420 --> 00:05:54,660
If there is only one, then also it will work.

109
00:05:54,660 --> 00:05:56,880
But we have made sure that if there are more

110
00:05:56,880 --> 00:05:59,640
than one include properties we can add them

111
00:05:59,640 --> 00:06:02,970
as a comma separated list and our repository

112
00:06:02,970 --> 00:06:05,580
is dynamic to handle that.

113
00:06:05,580 --> 00:06:08,250
Same logic that we have in get all.

114
00:06:08,250 --> 00:06:11,400
We will add that to get as well.

115
00:06:11,400 --> 00:06:13,890
So let me add that here.

116
00:06:13,890 --> 00:06:16,623
And we will add the include properties.

117
00:06:18,180 --> 00:06:19,710
Perfect.

118
00:06:19,710 --> 00:06:21,870
We have added the include properties

119
00:06:21,870 --> 00:06:25,590
in both get and get all repository.

120
00:06:25,590 --> 00:06:28,920
With that configured, let me close everything.

121
00:06:28,920 --> 00:06:31,290
Open the product controller.

122
00:06:31,290 --> 00:06:33,870
We do not need anything else here.

123
00:06:33,870 --> 00:06:36,090
And when we are getting all,

124
00:06:36,090 --> 00:06:38,790
we can define the include properties.

125
00:06:38,790 --> 00:06:41,853
We want to include category.

126
00:06:42,690 --> 00:06:46,140
Now right now I am intentionally adding a lowercase

127
00:06:46,140 --> 00:06:49,920
because I want to show you this will not work.

128
00:06:49,920 --> 00:06:51,780
So let me run the application

129
00:06:51,780 --> 00:06:55,623
with a lowercase category and see what happens.

130
00:06:56,820 --> 00:06:59,760
We go to product here and we get

131
00:06:59,760 --> 00:07:03,210
an exception with the include properties.

132
00:07:03,210 --> 00:07:06,630
You can see unable to find navigation category

133
00:07:06,630 --> 00:07:09,633
in the string based include path category.

134
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:14,430
That is because it does not find that navigation property.

135
00:07:14,430 --> 00:07:18,603
If you correct that case here and run it, it should work.

136
00:07:22,860 --> 00:07:24,990
Perfect, no exception this time.

137
00:07:24,990 --> 00:07:27,510
And if you examine the result here,

138
00:07:27,510 --> 00:07:31,683
category is populated and we have the category name.

139
00:07:32,700 --> 00:07:36,750
So finally we can display that in the absurd.

140
00:07:36,750 --> 00:07:38,340
In the index here.

141
00:07:38,340 --> 00:07:40,440
Let me go to the view.

142
00:07:40,440 --> 00:07:42,660
Where we have the category.

143
00:07:42,660 --> 00:07:47,253
We can navigate them by obj.category.name.

144
00:07:48,330 --> 00:07:51,030
Save that and continue.

145
00:07:51,030 --> 00:07:52,530
And perfect.

146
00:07:52,530 --> 00:07:54,824
Our category is being populated

147
00:07:54,824 --> 00:07:58,173
